      "id": "a1000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000006",
      "name": "Build Claude Prompt",
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const sourceContent = $input.item.json.data;\nconst selectedFile = $('Select Unprocessed File').item.json.selectedFile;\nconst postId = $('Select Unprocessed File').item.json.postId;\n\nconst prompt = `You are a cybersecurity expert and professional educator who shares insights on LinkedIn. Your audience includes IT professionals, cybersecurity practitioners, students, and business leaders interested in security.\n\nAnalyze the following educational content and create a compelling LinkedIn post based on the most interesting or important concept from it.\n\nRules:\n- Write 150-300 words\n- Start with a strong hook (question, surprising fact, or bold statement)\n- Use plain text only - NO markdown formatting (no **, no ##, no bullet points with -)\n- Use line breaks to separate paragraphs\n- End with 3-5 relevant hashtags on their own line\n- Be professional but conversational\n- Include a call-to-action or thought-provoking question at the end\n- Make it actionable - readers should learn something useful\n\nAlso create a DALL-E image prompt for a professional, visually striking image that complements this post. The image should be suitable for LinkedIn - clean, modern, and professional. Do NOT include any text in the image.\n\nRespond in valid JSON format only, with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"postText\": \"the full LinkedIn post text including hashtags\",\n  \"imagePrompt\": \"detailed DALL-E prompt for a complementary professional image\",\n  \"hashtags\": [\"hashtag1\", \"hashtag2\", \"hashtag3\"],\n  \"topicSummary\": \"2-3 word summary of the topic\"\n}\n\nSource content:\n${sourceContent}`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { prompt, selectedFile, postId, sourceContent } }];"
      },
      "position": [
        1460,
        -120
      ],
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2
